Fig. S14 (Supplementary data) indicates that the fluorescence intensity after labeling with the optimized Man–CQDs increased linearly with the logarithm of the concentration of E. coli (0–108
                        CFUmL−1), with a correlation coefficient of 0.991. The limit of detection (LOD; at an S/N ratio of 3) was approximately 100CFUmL−1 in a simple PBS solution. Moreover, we observed a similar relationship between the fluorescence intensity and concentration of E. coli-spiked real samples (tap water, apple juice, and human urine; Fig. 2
                        ), demonstrating the great potential of our Man–CQD probe for rapid bacterial screening in real samples.
